data.title: Connection with Coast and API Sales

moments.text: Harry from Canopy is mentioned as a connector. Excitement is expressed about the opportunity to connect with Coast.
The focus shifts to the API integration needs of enterprise clients. An inquiry is made about whether the API has started being sold.
A transition to enterprise clients is confirmed. The majority of new customers are expected to utilize the API for integration.
An API-based integration solution is discussed. A proof of concept is proposed to demonstrate functionality.
The web-based dashboard is described as straightforward. Data enrichment services are highlighted for smaller customers.
A comparison is made to a company called Nihilus. The functionality of embedding email threads into CRMs is mentioned.

data.title: Showcasing API Data in CRM Systems

moments.text: A structured CSV output of API data is presented. The data includes profile URL, name, city, and net worth estimation.
Machine learning is utilized for net worth estimations. Various data points such as company website and contact information are scraped.
The importance of integrating the application into existing systems is emphasized. The buyer often differs from the end user in larger firms.
Templates for different API use cases are discussed. The CRM template is highlighted as a key example.
The demo experience can be personalized for potential clients. Real-time API calls can impress prospects during presentations.
Customization options for demos include changing currencies and branding. The ability to visualize data through API calls is emphasized.
Concerns about current demand for visualization are expressed. The user interface is noted as clean and real-time updates are appreciated.
Setup time for the integration process is discussed. Self-service options for straightforward use cases are highlighted.
Interest in testing demos with potential clients is mentioned. The historical need for CRM integration is acknowledged.
A discussion about reconnecting in six months occurs. Different types of buyers and their needs are highlighted.
Pricing structure and proof of concept details are clarified. The annual agreement and scoping process for templates are explained.
Future collaboration and sharing of materials are discussed. A standard presentation deck will be sent for further review.

data.text: Coast's API integration is becoming increasingly relevant as enterprise clients seek to incorporate data into their existing systems rather than using a web-based application.
The potential for a demo swap was identified, allowing both parties to showcase their platforms and explore integration possibilities.
Coast's current demand for API visualization tools is low, with Jakob noting, "I just don't know if we have the demand for this right now."
A follow-up in six months is suggested to reassess the need for API integration solutions as Coast continues to push into enterprise markets.
